description: Test for intermittent voltage fluctuations or instability in the ambient sensor module's relay driver circuit—especially check for defective or degraded capacitors in the relay control timing or hold circuit, which may cause momentary drops leading to relay chatter and lamp blinking., outcome='Voltage at the control relay measures 11.9873 V on the positive port and 0.3592 V on the negative port. Voltage at the timing potentiometer measures 11.9873 V on the positive port and 0.0003 V on the negative port, with the wiper port disconnected. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module relay contacts (output switching action),
description: Measure the relay's contact resistance and monitor for intermittent opening or high resistance using an ohmmeter or voltage drop measurement while the lamp is observed. This checks for relay contact bounce, wear, or faulty action that could cause periodic loss of voltage to the load., outcome='Relay contact resistance is nominal at 0.01 Ω, matching the expected value. The voltage measured at the lamp is essentially zero (0.0003 V), and the lamp is not lit. There are no intermittent openings or high resistance detected in the relay contacts during this test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module cable input connectors,
description: While the lamp is observed to blink off, wiggle and gently move the cable connectors at the load module input (where cables from the control module connect) to test for intermittent or momentary disconnection or contact fault at the terminal, which may cause the load to drop out periodically., outcome='The main load (lamp) is currently not lit and shows no observable internal fault. The connections at the load module input are as follows: Load Input Cable (+) is connected to Control Output Cable (+), and Load Input Cable (−) is connected to Control Output Cable (−). No polarity inversion is detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module internal wiring (lamp and indicator common point to input),
description: Measure continuity and resistance between the load module input terminals and the common wiring point that feeds both the main lamp and indicator lamp. This checks for any internal wiring break or loose connection within the load module causing both lamps to periodically lose power, despite nominal upstream voltages and verified components., outcome="Continuity tests show a resistive path present from 'Load Input Cable (+)' to both the main lamp and indicator lamp (98.48 Ω), as well as from 'Load Input Cable (−)' to both lamps (96.87 Ω). No polarity inversion detected. There are no open circuit conditions in the tested wiring paths.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module,
description: Test the load module with an external 12V DC power supply, independently of the upstream modules, by directly connecting 12V and 0V to the load input cables. Observe if the lamp exhibits the same periodic blinking behavior. This will help determine if the fault is within the load module itself or due to upstream module behavior., outcome='The Main Load (lamp) was visually inspected and is currently not lit. No observable internal faults were found in the lamp.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module input voltage (during external 12V supply),
description: Measure the voltage at the load module input terminals while powering the load module with an external 12V supply and the module is observed to be not lit. This determines if voltage is actually reaching the load module terminals and can clarify whether there is an internal or wiring fault preventing power from reaching the lamps., outcome='The voltage measured at the Load Input Cable (+) is approximately 0.36 V, and at the Load Input Cable (−) is approximately 0.0003 V. This indicates that the expected 12V is not present at the load module input terminals. Power is not reaching the load module.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module output cable (+) terminal (at control module end),
description: Measure the voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) directly at its terminal inside the control module, both during normal operation and during attempts to power the load module with an external supply (with all control/load interconnections disconnected). This will clarify whether there is a short or cross-feed from the control module output that is shunting away the voltage applied to the load module, which could explain the low measured voltage at the load module input regardless of power source., outcome='Voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) terminal inside the control module was measured at 0.3592 V (relative to ground) during both normal operation and when the load module was powered externally with all interconnections disconnected. There were no changes between test conditions, and no polarity inversion was detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module Control Output Cable (+) disconnection/isolation check,
description: Disconnect the Control Output Cable (+) from the rest of the circuit at both ends (at the control module and at the load module), then measure the resistance to ground and to the negative terminal from each end of the cable. Also check for continuity or low resistance to any other cables. This will test whether there is an internal short or cross-connection between the Control Output Cable (+) and another part of the circuit., outcome='Continuity for Control Output Cable (+) is nominal. There is a short (low resistance) between Control Output Cable (+) and Control Input Cable (+), PSU Output Cable (+), and Load Input Cable (+), indicating direct electrical connection to these points. All connections to negative cables or terminals show resistive (not shorted) paths. No POLARITY INVERSION detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=230.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module Output Cable (+),
description: With the system completely powered down and all modules disconnected, test the continuity between the power supply module output cable (+) and all other (+) cables—including Control Input Cable (+), Control Output Cable (+), and Load Input Cable (+). Also measure resistance between the power supply (+) and ground/negative. This will clarify if an unintended internal short, tie, or direct wiring issue exists upstream that could be shunting voltage from the entire chain., outcome='Continuity tests show a very low-resistance short (<0.4 Ω) between PSU Output Cable (+) and all other (+) cables: Control Input (+), Control Output (+), and Load Input (+). There is also a low-resistance path (1.0 Ω) between PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−). No polarity inversion is detected in these measurements, but these results indicate strong continuity and a near-short to ground/negative.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module (internal short to ground or case),
description: With all modules disconnected, measure resistance between the Load Input Cable (+) and Load Input Cable (−), and from each to the module case/ground. This will test for an internal short inside the load module which could explain the exceptionally low resistance reading from PSU Output Cable (+) to ground., outcome="Measured resistance between Load Input Cable (+) and Load Input Cable (−) is 1.61 Ω, indicating a resistive path. Resistance to the module case/ground could not be measured due to lack of measurable affordance on the 'Load Cube'. No polarity inversion is indicated by these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module internal parallel paths (auxiliary connections, lamp & indicator housings),
description: With all modules disconnected and the load module isolated, measure resistance and continuity between all possible internal circuit nodes—across the main lamp, indicator lamp, diode, and input wires. Map out the resistance between every pair of points to look for an unintended low-resistance parallel path (e.g., solder bridge, conductive debris, misplaced wire, or short) that would account for the 1–2 Ω resistance across the load input, which should not be present in normal operation., outcome='All component-to-cable resistance measurements are in the expected range except for the resistance measured directly between Load Input Cable (+) and Load Input Cable (−), which is 1.61 Ω, indicating an unintended low-resistance path between the input cables. Additionally, the resistance from the Load Protection Diode to Load Input Cable (+) is extremely low (0.1 Ω), suggesting a near-short between these points. No polarity inversion was detected in these connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=310.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
